##Key Concepts 

--- Cloud run--- Serveless comput platform, has 2 identities 
* invoker identity -> controls who can call the service 
* runtime service account (SA) -> controls what the service can access 

- To access clould SQL, cloud run uses the runtime SA, not the invoker or the 
user
- Deploying Cloud Run with a custom SA required roles/iam.serviceAccountUser on
that SA 


--- Cloud SQL Private IP---
Requires : 
* servicenetworking.googleapis.com enabled
* a reserved/24 address block
* a VPC peering connection with google managed services

- Cloud SQL Private IP appears in the VPC internal range, not the public
-Cloud run -> cloud SQL Requiers:
* a Serverless VPC connector 
* The tuntime SA to have roles/cloudsql.client

---Serverless VPC Access---
* connects the cloud run to the internal resources inside your VPC 
- Must be created with a /28 CIDR
- without this connector, cloud run cannot see Private Ips or Cloud SQL

